Chelsea boss, Frank Lampard, has confirmed that winger, Christian Pulisic, is part of the Blues’ squad to face Wolves in the Premier League on Tuesday night at the Molineux Stadium. Lampard said this on Monday during his pre-match press conference while providing an update on Pulisic. Chelsea head to the game following a 1-0 defeat against Everton in the Premier League over the weekend.’ ”Christian Pulisic trained on the day we played against Everton and felt better,” Lampard said. “He’s in the squad tomorrow, and it’s yet to be decided whether he starts or not. “It’s obviously positive news from the weekend.” The kick-off time for the match is 7 pm.